            . I am a <rs id="t18331128-165-viclabel922" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-165-victim1658 t18331128-165-viclabel922"></join>, and live in Duke-street, Aldgate. On Saturday, the 20th of October, I was in <placeName id="t18331128-165-crimeloc923">Aldgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-165-crimeloc923" type="placeName" value="Aldgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-165-crimeloc923" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-165-off920 t18331128-165-crimeloc923"></join>, between two and three o'clock in the day time - I had my snuff-box in my coat-pocket; I felt a tug at my pocket, turned round, and a gentleman said, "You have been robbed, and the person who robbed you is opposite;" and pointed him out - I ran over, laid hold of the prisoner, and said, "You rascal, what have you been robbing me for," and the box fell from between his shirt and waistband; I gave him in charge - it was concealed under his waistband.</p>
